description: Human-readable name for the type of calendar.
The ordinal position of the period within the annual period.
Unique ID denoting a type of calendar (e.g., Month, Quarter, Retail 4-5-4 Month).
The last day of the period.
The first day of the period.
The year number related to the annual calendar for the period. It reflects the calendar year for calendar periods and the 4-5-4 retail year for retail periods.
